R Notebook

Common markers for preadipocytes in mice are PDGFRA, LY6A (ATXN1 in humans), CD34, PREF1 (=DLK1 gene in humans) and CD29 (=ITGB1 gene in humans). PPARG = mature adipocyte marker.

Grouped by cluster.

Negative markers cluster 12 with the highest negative log fold change. Interesting to see HIST1H4C is expressed in two groups in the other clusters. Furthermore, there are a lot of COL genes in the list downregulated (13). COL genes encode for collagen proteins.

Complete list of markers for cluster 12.
